  "texts": [
    "This profile can then be used to generate granular real-time predictions about voting patterns for the next election.",
    "Is your privacy violated?",
    "Following Rubinstein (2014), our understanding of privacy is twofold.",
    "On the one hand, there is information privacy, i.e., citizens' ability to control information about themselves and determine the extent of authorised disclosure (Warren and Brandeis 1989; Fried 1970; Parent 1983; Westin 1968).",
    "On the other hand, there is political privacy, defined as a protected personal sphere of deliberation and decision-making (see for instance: Brettschneider (2009))."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Following Rubinstein (2014), our understanding of privacy is twofold.",
    "On the one hand, there is information privacy, i.e., citizens' ability to control information about themselves and determine the extent of authorised disclosure (Warren and Brandeis 1989; Fried 1970; Parent 1983; Westin 1968).",
    "On the other hand, there is political privacy, defined as a protected personal sphere of deliberation and decision-making (see for instance: Brettschneider (2009))."
  ]
}